## Tone & Copy
- Australian English: recognised, organised, colour, licence (noun)
- B2B tone for ANZ CFOs and Finance Directors
- Messaging: governance, audit confidence, EOFY outcomes, Board accountability
- Key phrases: "audit-defensible", "EOFY-ready", "Board accountability"
- Avoid implementation/configuration language — focus on business outcomes

## Editing Rules
1. Nav/header/footer change → apply to ALL .html files simultaneously
2. Never rename or remove existing CSS classes
3. Check css/styles.css before adding any new class — reuse existing ones
4. Preserve the inline <script> at bottom of every page
5. All href paths are relative (e.g. href="css/styles.css", not absolute)
6. No inline styles — all CSS goes in css/styles.css

## Contact Form — DO NOT MODIFY
- Salesforce Web-to-Lead: do not change form action URL or hidden field values (OID etc.)
- Post-submit redirect: thank-you.html

## NEVER DO
- Add npm / package.json / node_modules / build tools
- Use Bootstrap, Tailwind, or any CSS framework
- Add inline styles
- Modify Salesforce form hidden fields
- Re-add "Start with a Governance Snapshot" to the nav
- Use absolute paths for local resources
